{
  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONMarket demand is high for valuable and efficient systems and algorithms that can give concise advice or conclusions from big datasets [1].",
    "A major challenge of information extraction is a frequent lack of sufficiently labeled data for training machine learning algorithms due to labor intensiveness and cost of acquiring labels [2].",
    "Generating synthetic datasets is often quite useful, particularly for testing purposes in numerous areas of computing, including artificial intelligence, data mining, data visualization and software engineering [3].",
    "The sizes of samples, rules, and attributes of the synthetic datasets can be readily adjusted to meet the needs of evaluating various learning algorithms [1].",
    "With synthetic data, attributes such as missing values, dimensions, outliers, data format and type, trends, and patterns can be controlled [4]."
  ]
}